{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"06561e8e156675bfe4c4ab6d116d69a0","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nWhen `cluster_consult` detects a stale factsheet (`src/clusterConsult.ts:62-78`):\n\n1. **Detect**: `findStaleFiles()` compares current SHA-256 hashes + file sizes against stored `cluster_file_hashes` — any mismatch → stale\n2. **Mark**: `db.markClusterFactsheetStale(factsheetId)` sets factsheet and cluster status to `stale`/`untrusted`\n3. **Log**: `cluster_refresh_required` event with `changed_files` list\n4. **Return**: `CLUSTER_FACTSHEET_STALE` error\n\nThe caller-facing MCP layer (`src/tools.ts:781-817`) then runs a fallback cascade:\n\n- **Retry once** — re-probe availability and call `consultCluster` again (catches race where another process refreshed)\n- **Strict evidence revalidation** (if `autoRefresh = true`) — per-cluster lock, re-checks every selector/snippet_hash; if all pass, re-calls `consultCluster`; if any fails, falls through\n- **Fallback to V1** `claude_consult` — marks cluster `needs_prepare`, answers via normal session routing, logs `cluster_fallback_to_claude_consult`\n\nThe caller only sees `CLUSTER_FACTSHEET_STALE` if `autoRefresh = false` or the error is `CLUSTER_PROJECT_MISMATCH` (a security boundary that must always be surfaced)."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":132649,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1bc568d1-5a5f-4314-b4be-00aca006f5e1","uuid":"357b7bb7-fbb9-42c0-b79d-dfca2867b903"}
